Seahorse Spark docker image
===========================

The image contains Spark and python libraries required for running SX inside a docker container.

1. Building the image

   $ docker build -t quay.io/deepsense_io/deepsense-spark:2.0.0 .

2. Running the image

   $ docker run -h sandbox -d quay.io/deepsense_io/deepsense-spark:2.0.0
   $ docker run -it -p 8088:8088 -p 8042:8042 -p 4040:4040 -h sandbox quay.io/deepsense_io/deepsense-spark:2.0.0 bash

3. Publishing the image

   $ docker push quay.io/deepsense_io/deepsense-spark:2.0.0

4. Verifying R libraries:
To verify possibility of installation of popular machine learning R packages,
run in R Notebook (in Local, default preset) and investigate for non-zero exit codes:

# http://www.kdnuggets.com/2015/06/top-20-r-machine-learning-packages.html
install.packages("e1071")
install.packages("rpart")
install.packages("igraph")
install.packages("nnet")
install.packages("randomForest")
install.packages("caret")
install.packages("kernlab")
install.packages("glmnet")
install.packages("ROCR")
install.packages("gbm")
install.packages("party")
install.packages("arules")
install.packages("tree")
install.packages("klaR")
install.packages("RWeka")
install.packages("ipred")
install.packages("lars")
install.packages("earth")
install.packages("CORElearn")
install.packages("mboost")

